The Republicans hold a majority of governorships, of state legislative chambers, and are a force to be reckoned with in contests for statewide and local office from the East Coast to the West Coast and from the North to the South. This is not to suggest they are winning everything – or even most things – as much as it suggests that the potential to create a powerful, national political force exists when everyone does their homework and all the oars are being pulled in the same direction at the same time.
